It is steamed dumpling with different stuffing. Today we are making veg momos on your huge demand. These turn out really yummy. This is authentic north Indian style recipe. This can be a good variation for your evening snack or even breakfast. It is very easy and simple recipe. You can try this recipe at home and drop a comment for me. Do not forget to like, share and subscribe.Ingredients:‚Ä¢ 1 cup finely grated Cabbage‚Ä¢ 1/2 cup finely grated Carrot‚Ä¢ Finely chopped Onion‚Ä¢ Salt to taste‚Ä¢ 1 cup Maida‚Ä¢ Salt to taste‚Ä¢ 1 tsp Oil‚Ä¢ Water‚Ä¢ Finely chopped Garlic‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp grated Ginger‚Ä¢ Finely chopped Green chili‚Ä¢ Black pepper powder‚Ä¢ Finely chopped Coriander leaves (Optional)Method:‚Ä¢ Take cabbage, carrot, onion, salt in a strainer and mix well. ‚Ä¢ Rest the veggies mixture aside for about 30 minutes. ‚Ä¢ Take maida in a dish and add salt, oil. ‚Ä¢ You can use wheat flour in place of maida. ‚Ä¢ Mix well and add a little water at a time to knead a little stiff dough. ‚Ä¢ Cover and rest the dough for about 30 minutes. ‚Ä¢ Squeeze out as much water as possible from the veggies and transfer into a bowl. ‚Ä¢ You can use the squeezed water for making dal or for making vegetable soup. ‚Ä¢ Add garlic, ginger, green chili, black pepper powder, coriander leaves to the veggies and mix   well. ‚Ä¢  Adding coriander leaves is optional. You can skip it if you don‚Äôt want. ‚Ä¢ Stuffing is ready. ‚Ä¢ Take the dough and knead it once to make smooth and even. ‚Ä¢ Make small balls form the dough and make them smooth and even. ‚Ä¢ Take one dough ball and roll it into as thin disc as possible. ‚Ä¢ Fill the stuffing and begin to fold from the center of the disc to make plates. ‚Ä¢ Lift the other half edge and close it up with the plates. Seal it well. ‚Ä¢ Grease the steamer dish well with oil and transfer the momos into it. ‚Ä¢ You can steam the momos in idly plates or even in a dish.‚Ä¢ Steam momos on medium heat for just 10 minutes. ‚Ä¢ Remove the lid and take the momos out. ‚Ä¢ Momos are all ready. ‚Ä¢ You can make around 17-18 momos from 1 cup maida.For more Such Recipes‡§ù‡§ü‡§™‡§ü ‡§¨‡§®‡§µ‡§æ ‡§á‡§Ç‡§¶‡•ã‡§∞ ‡§∏‡•ç‡§™‡•á‡§∂‡§≤ ‡§Æ‡§ä‡§∏‡•Ç‡§¶ ‡§ñ‡§Æ‡§® ‡§á‡§°‡§≤‡•Ä | Instant Soft Khaman Idli | Street Food | MadhurasRecipe - https://youtu.be/ldsSt9wvDmM‡§ï‡•Å‡§∞‡§ï‡•Å‡§∞‡•Ä‡§§ ‡§™‡§æ‡§≤‡§ï ‡§™‡§ï‡•ã‡§°‡§æ | Crispy Palak Pakoda | Street Style Palak Pakoda | MadhurasRecipe | Ep - 428 - https://youtu.be/HznLimdB9SM‡§ö‡§ü‡§™‡§ü‡•Ä‡§§ ‡§™‡§®‡•Ä‡§∞ ‡§´‡•ç‡§∞‡§Å‡§ï‡•Ä  | Street Style Tawa Paneer Frankie Recipe | MadhurasRecipe | Ep - 429 - https://youtu.be/vaoOg-_gMos‡§ö‡§ü‡§™‡§ü‡•Ä‡§§ ‡§§‡§µ‡§æ ‡§™‡•Å‡§≤‡§æ‡§µ | Quick Tawa Pulao Recipe | Street Style Tawa Pulao | MadhurasRecipe | Ep - 400 - https://youtu.be/uX68yDLgpE4‡§∂‡•á‡§µ ‡§¨‡§ü‡§æ‡§ü‡§æ ‡§¶‡§π‡•Ä ‡§™‡•Å‡§∞‡•Ä  | SPDP | Sev Batata Dahi Puri | Indian Street Food | MadhurasRecipe | Ep - 316 - https://youtu.be/1ApccuUo8xM‡§ö‡§ü‡§™‡§ü‡•Ä‡§§ ‡§∞‡§ó‡§°‡§æ ‡§™‡•Ö‡§ü‡•Ä‡§∏  | Ragada Patties Recipe | Indian Street Food | MadhurasRecipe | Ep - 313 - https://youtu.be/R_5XUVvITxo‡§™‡§æ‡§µ ‡§≠‡§æ‡§ú‡•Ä  | Pav Bhaji Recipe by madhurasrecipe | Indian Street Food - https://youtu.be/A8V8jj7sbZs‡§™‡§æ‡§£‡•Ä ‡§™‡•Å‡§∞‡•Ä‡§∏‡§æ‡§†‡•Ä ‡§™‡§æ‡§£‡•Ä | How to make Pani for Pani Puri | MadhurasRecipe | Ep - 308 - https://youtu.be/kEPOC4nd3GE‡§™‡§æ‡§£‡•Ä ‡§™‡•Å‡§∞‡•Ä ‡§ö‡•Ä ‡§™‡•Å‡§∞‡•Ä | Puri for Pani Puri | How to make Golgappa Puri | MadhurasRecipe | Ep - 309 - https://youtu.be/LNyVUYny-JE‡§ö‡§Æ‡§ö‡§Æ‡•Ä‡§§ ‡§ì‡§≤‡•Ä ‡§≠‡•á‡§≥ | Oli Bhel Recipe | How to make Bhel | Bhel Puri Recipe | MadhurasRecipe - https://youtu.be/IgwJPgEE9V4

So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:--------------------------------------------------------------------The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in Gokuldham Co-operative Society and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' (Dilip Joshi) who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Shailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi / Raj Anadkat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. But today in this recipe you will learn to knead dough without dirtying your hands, how to make quick chapattis and how these chapattis can remain soft longer. These chapattis get nice layers and remain soft for longer time. You can try this recipe home and drop a comment for me. Do not forget to like, share and subscribe.Ingredients:‚Ä¢ 3 cups Wheat flour‚Ä¢ 3/4 tsp Salt‚Ä¢ 1 1/4 cup Water‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp Oil‚Ä¢ Oil for spreading on chapatti Method:‚Ä¢ In a bowl take wheat flour, salt and mix it well with spatula. ‚Ä¢ Add a little water at a time and continue mixing the flour with spatula. ‚Ä¢ Continue mixing until it comes together really good. ‚Ä¢ Clean the spatula and knead the dough. Continue kneading the dough for about a minute or   so. ‚Ä¢ Dust dry flour and clean the pot. Spread oil on the dough and knead it a little again to make it   smooth and even. ‚Ä¢ Again spread a little oil on the dough, cover and rest it for about 15-20 minutes. ‚Ä¢ If you are making the chapattis after some time then spread water instead of oil and rest the   dough. ‚Ä¢ Take the dough and knead it once more to make smooth and even. ‚Ä¢ Make small balls of dough. ‚Ä¢ Take one dough ball and make it smooth and even. ‚Ä¢ Dip it in dry flour and knead it into a small disc. ‚Ä¢ Spread a little oil and fold into half. ‚Ä¢ Again spread a little oil and fold it into quarter. ‚Ä¢ This will give you 3 layered chapattis. ‚Ä¢ For making 2 layered chapattis dip a dough ball into dry flour and roll a small oval disc. ‚Ä¢ Spread a little oil and pinch it at the center. ‚Ä¢ Fold it and roll it into chapatti to make 2 layered chapatti. ‚Ä¢ To save time keep the folded chapattis ready before rolling. ‚Ä¢ When you begin to fold the dough balls then you can turn on the gas to heat up the skillet. This   will help you to make chapattis quickly. ‚Ä¢ Take a folded disc and dip it in dry flour. ‚Ä¢ Roll round chapatti carefully. ‚Ä¢ The edges should be thin and center should be equally thin. ‚Ä¢ Transfer the chapatti on the skillet and roast from one side until small bubbles begin to appear   on upper side.  ‚Ä¢ When upper surface dries a little, changes the color flip the chapatti over and spread a little oil   on it. ‚Ä¢ Flip over and spread a little oil on other side too. ‚Ä¢ Roast chapatti well from both sides and take it off on a jali. ‚Ä¢ Soft chapatti is all ready. ‚Ä¢ You can make around 9-10 chapattis from 3 cups flour.For more Such Recipes‡§ò‡§°‡•Ä‡§ö‡•Ä ‡§™‡•ã‡§≥‡•Ä | Ghadhichi Poli by madhurasrecipe | How to make Soft Roti Pudachi Poli | Cooking -
